ancreatic cancer and passed away in 2006, he and his family wanted to start a foundation to directly help people who were not as fortunate to have the means to handle many hardships that come with this disease. Ryan has been working as a financial advisor for Raymond James &amp; Associates since March of 2020. He spends much of his time out and about with his wife Rachel and their 18 month old son Benjamin. They are also excited to welcome their new addition to the family early next year.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Ryan Gordon','','publish','open','closed','','ryan-gordon','','','2024-09-26 11:28:50','2024-09-26 11:28:50','',0,'https://andyschramfoundation.org/?post_type=founder&#038;p=544',0,'founder','',0),(545,1,'2024-08-29 11:10:59','2024-08-29 11:10:59','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Christina Krajcsik is a realtor with Keller Williams Real Estate in Langhorne. She comes from a very close family and family has always been #1. She is excited to serve on this incredible board for many reasons. Christina lost both of my grandmother\'s to Pancreatic Cancer so this cause is very near and dear to her heart. She is eager to be more involved with this amazing community and serve in any way that she can to help those affected by this horrible disease.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Christina Krajcsik','','publish','open','closed','','christina-krajcsik','','','2024-09-26 11:28:22','2024-09-26 11:28:22','',0,'https://andyschramfoundation.org/?post_type=founder&#038;p=545',0,'founder','',0),(547,1,'2024-08-29 11:12:17','2024-08-29 11:12:17','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Samuel Foster is a Philadelphia native currently located in Cherry Hill, NJ. Samuel\'s Father, William, was diagnosed with Pancreatic Cancer in 2016 and underwent his surgery &amp; treatment at Jefferson in Philadelphia. Samuel left his job in Missouri to return home and become a joint caretaker of his Father. Samuel\'s Father passed away in August of 2018, with his family creating the \"W. Kim Foster Pancreatic Cancer Collaborative Research Space\" and an endowed research fund in 2019. Professionally, Sam is a Director of Strategic Operations at a Fortune 10 Healthcare Company where he strives to reduce cost and improve the quality of care received by patients across the US.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Samuel Foster','','publish','open','closed','','samuel-foster','','','2024-09-26 11:27:47','2024-09-26 11:27:47','',0,'https://andyschramfoundation.org/?post_type=founder&#038;p=547',0,'founder','',0),(548,1,'2024-08-29 11:13:21','2024-08-29 11:13:21','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Jared Miller is a dedicated advocate for pancreatic cancer awareness and support, deeply inspired by his mother\'s seven-and-a-half-year battle with the disease. Just three days before she passed, his mother fulfilled a bucket list dream by seeing The Book of Mormon in New York City, where she laughed with all her heart. This moment of joy amidst adversity led Jared to conceive the idea of Laugh My Pancre-Ass Off™, a comedy event celebrating the power of laughter even in the face of serious illness.<br><br>Jared is proud to be part of the Andy Schram Foundation, where he continues his mission to turn personal loss into a source of hope and strength for others.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Jared Miller','','publish','open','closed','','jared-miller','','','2024-09-26 11:26:40','2024-09-26 11:26:40','',0,'https://andyschramfoundation.org/?post_type=founder&#038;p=548',0,'founder','',0),(549,1,'2024-08-29 11:14:10','2024-08-29 11:14:10','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Carina Rosario is a Center Director and Operational Leader for Heart &amp; Paw Veterinary Care. As a business professional who practices servant and transformational leadership, Carina was motivated to use her drive and compassion to help others in her personal life. The opportunity to serve on this board is significant to Carina. She sees The Andy Schram Foundation as a way to honor the people close to her who have lost loved ones to pancr